Spy Movement (Moving into neighboring districts) – This was next on our list, introducing the ability for spies to move into valid neighboring districts.
Spy Embedding and Resource Generation – Once a spy is in a district not controlled by its owner, it can be embedded, generating resources (gold and intel) while losing the ability to move until reactivated.
Spy Drawing on the Game Board (Visual Representation) – Visual feedback to show spies on the game board, so the player knows where spies are located.
Adding Spy Count to UI (District Information and Turn Information) – Displaying the number of spies in the district and turn summary.